data.name: CheckBox18.ToolTip
data.value: Run scripting command once in the main menu. For example to start a certain SP mission of choice automatically. Example: -init=playMission["","M04Saboteur.Sara"]. The Mission has to reside in the "arma2\Missions" folder, NOT the user directory. (-init)

data.name: CheckBox7.ToolTip
data.value: Forces the game to use Direct3D version 9 only, not the extended Vista / Win7 Direct3D 9Ex the most visible feature the Direct3D 9Ex version offers is a lot faster alt-tabing. May help with problems using older drivers on multi-GPU systems (-winXP)

data.name: CheckBox5.ToolTip
data.value: Defines Video Memory allocation limit to number (in MegaBytes). Use to resolve e.g. Windows problems. 128 is hard-coded minimum (anything lower falls backs to 128). 2047 is soft-coded maximum. (-maxVRAM)

data.name: CheckBox4.ToolTip
data.value: Defines memory allocation limit to number (in MegaBytes). 256 is hard-coded minimum (anything lower falls backs to 256). 2047 is hard-coded maximum (anything higher falls back to 2047). Engine uses automatic values (512-1536 MB) w/o maxMem parameter. Yet FileCache was always excluded from the virtual address limit (-maxMem)
